example of follow up  mail to recruter
#############################################

Subject: Follow-Up on [Job Title] Application

Dear [Recruiter's Name],

I hope this email finds you well. I wanted to follow up on my recent application for the [Job Title] position at [Company Name]. I am extremely interested in this opportunity and would like to thank you for considering me for the role.

As a highly motivated and detail-oriented individual, I am confident that my skills and experience align well with the requirements of the position. I have a proven track record of success in [relevant experience or skill], and I believe that I would make a valuable contribution to the [Company Name] team.

I would greatly appreciate the opportunity to discuss my application with you in more detail and answer any questions you may have. If it would be convenient, I would be happy to schedule a call or in-person meeting at your earliest convenience.

Thank you again for your time and consideration. I look forward to hearing back from you soon.

Best regards,
[Your Name]


###########################################################
example of message to send to the hiring manager
###########################################################

Subject: Interest in the Senior DevOps Engineer Position

Dear [Hiring Manager's Name],

I came across your posting for the Senior DevOps Engineer position on [platform/website] and I am very interested in the opportunity. I have over [X] years of experience in the field of DevOps and I am confident that my skills and experience align with the requirements of the role.

I am particularly impressed with [Company's Name]'s reputation for innovation and the use of cutting-edge technologies in the industry. As a highly experienced and motivated DevOps Engineer, I am excited about the prospect of contributing to the company's continued success.

I have a solid understanding of the software development process and my experience with automation, CI/CD, and infrastructure management makes me well-suited for this role. I have also led remote teams and have successfully managed and mentored junior engineers to help them develop new skills and advance in their careers.

I am excited about the opportunity to learn more about the position and the team and I would love to discuss how I can contribute to the company's success. Can we schedule a call to discuss further? Please let me know what would be a convenient time for you.

Thank you for considering my application. I look forward to hearing from you.

Best regards,
[Your Name]

